- tags (list of labels): are flexible multi-dimensional metadata used for filtering, ad-hoc selection, or feature flags (e.g., `gpu`, `mobile`, `intel`, `wifi-only`, `wazuh-agent`). Tags can be many-to-many and are good for grouping and selecting hosts for deployments, monitoring, or policy exceptions.
